title: darumaka
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #554 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Fire type PokÃ©mon.
Darumaka is a round, red PokÃ©mon with an orange face and yellow curly eyebrows. It has three yellow ovals on its abdomen and a curvy yellow line on its back. Its paws are orange and have three digits each.

It evolves into [[Darmanitan]]
Japanese Name: [b]Darumakka[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Krookodile]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Darmanitan]]

title: krookodile
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #553 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a dual type Ground/Dark PokÃ©mon.
Krookodile has a thick maroon-colored body, black back, and white stomach. It has five triangular spikes on its back: four around the middle of its back, and one large one at the beginning of its tail. Each of the smaller spikes on its back are linked to black, triangular spikes that reach around to its front, slightly overlapping its white stomach. The largest spike sits at the beginning of its long thick tail, which has three, thick, black stripes.

It evolves from [[Krokorok]].
Japanese Name: [b]Waruvial[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Krokorok]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Darumaka]]

title: krokorok
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]]  #552 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a dual type Ground/Dark PokÃ©mon.
Krokorok is a reptilian PokÃ©mon with a mostly tan body, pink stomach, black back, and long tail. It is classified as a quadruped, though it is more often seen on two legs. It has six thick, black stripes on its body: one at shoulder level, one around its midsection, one around its hips, and three on its tail. Each stripe is topped with a triangular spike on its back.

It evolves from [[Sandile]] and evolves into [[Krookodile]].
Japanese Name: [b]Waruvile[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Sandile]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Krookodile]]

title: sandile
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #551 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a dual type Ground/Dark PokÃ©mon.
Sandile is a short, quadruped with a long snout and tail. Its body is mostly light brown with the exception of black stripes crossing over and under its legs and its pink underbelly. It has a black stripe on its snout in front of its eyes, and black covering the tip of its tail. Its eyes resemble binoculars and are shrouded in black all around their front.

It evolves into [[Krokorok]].
Japanese Name: [b]Meguroco[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Basculin]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Krokorok]]

title: whirlipede
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #544 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a dual type Bug/Poison PokÃ©mon.
Whirlipede is an insectoid PokÃ©mon encased in a hard, segmented shell. It has two pairs of gray, horn-like feelers with dark gray stripes, with one pair extended upward from its front and the other pointing downward from its lower rear. Two poisonous barbs flank either side of each segment of its shell. The shell itself is gray, with red rings in the middle of each segment and a darker gray border circling its open center. 

It evolves from [[Venipede]] and evolves into [[Scolipede]].
Japanese Name: [b]Wheega[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Venipede]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Scolipede]]

title: venipede
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #543 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a dual type Bug/Poison PokÃ©mon.
Venipede is an insectoid PokÃ©mon with a pronounced hump on the upper portion of its body. Its thorax and head are mainly magenta with black markings that consist of rings on its shoulders, a band around each antenna, and an upside-down 'Y' on its neck. A prominent ridge leading down to a pointed tip splits the top half of its head, and its lower jaw is black. It has round, heavy-lidded eyes that bulge away from the head slightly.

It evolves into [[Whirlipede]]
Japanese Name: [b]Fushide[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Leavanny]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Whirlipede]]

title: sawk
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #539 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Fighting type PokÃ©mon.
Sawk is a bipedal, humanoid PokÃ©mon with a lean, blue body and rocky skin. Its head is oblong-like and low on its shoulders, with an ornate sideways z-shaped black feature that forms its nose and its left brow. Its hands and feet each have three digits, with its feet and toes coming to a sharp point. It wears a light blue Karate gi with a black, v-neck collar that extends down to its black belt. 
It is always male.

Japanese Name: [b]Dageki[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Throh]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Sewaddle]]

title: throh
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #538  in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Fighting type PokÃ©mon.
Throh is a bipedal, humanoid PokÃ©mon with a bulky, red body and rocky skin. Its head is round and low on its shoulders with a T-shaped black feature that forms its nose and brow. Its hands and feet each have three digits, with its fingers being rounded. It wears a white judogi with a black, v-neck collar that extends down to its black belt. The gi has an integrate diamond pattern on its sleeves and a black, square patch on the bend of its knees.
This PokÃ©mon is always male.

Japanese Name: [b]Nageki[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Seismitoad]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Sawk]]

title: seismitoad
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #537 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a dual type Water/Ground PokÃ©mon.
Seismitoad is a bulky, blue, bipedal toad-like PokÃ©mon. Its underside and the speaker-like bumps found on various parts of its body are cyan with black edges around the belly. Its hands and feet have three bulbous digits. Additionally, Seismitoad have red eyes, cyan adornments on its legs, and a long tongue.

It evolves from [[Palpitoad]].
Japanese Name: [b]Gamageroge[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Palpitoad]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Throh]]

title: palpitoad
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #536 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a dual type Water/GRound PokÃ©mon.
Palpitoad is an amphibious, bipedal PokÃ©mon with an ovoid body. It is mostly blue, with a tan oval marking lined with black stretching from the bottom of its belly to its forehead. Its black eyes are round. Its upper lip is round as well, and curves down sharply at the corners.

It evolves from [[Tympole]] and evolves into [[Seismitoad]].
Japanese Name: [b]Gamagaru[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Tympole]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Seismitoad]]

title: tympole
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #535 in the National PokÃ©mon, a Water type PokÃ©mon.
Tympole is a round, tadpole-like PokÃ©mon with a tan, circular face. It has large, oval, black eyes, a wide mouth with down-turned corners, and black eyebrows in the shape of quarter notes. Its spherical body is black with no visible limbs. Instead, it has two black-and-blue ringed half-spheres on either side of its head.

It evolves into [[Palpitoad]].
Japanese Name: [b]Otamaro[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Conkeldurr]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Palpitoad]]

title: conkeldurr
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #534 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Fighting type PokÃ©mon.
Conkeldurr is a bipedal sepia-colored PokÃ©mon resembling an ogre. Its nose is large and red, with its face also having a prominent brow, a wide mouth, a gray tuft on its chin, dark rings around its eyes and a bulbous feature sticking up from the back of its head.

It evolves from [[Gurdurr]] when traded.
Japanese Name: [b]Roubushin[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Gurdurr]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Tympole]]

title: drilbur
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #529 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Ground type PokÃ©mon.
Drilbur has a short, wide body with two small, ovoid feet with three toes each. Its body is mostly black, but has a jagged, navy blue stripe that runs diagonally around its torso from its left shoulder. It is connected at the bottom to another stripe, which extends around the base of its torso. 

It evolves into [[Excadrill]].
Japanese Name: [b]Mogurew[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Swoobat]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Excadrill]]

title: swoobat
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #528 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a dual type Psychic/Flying PokÃ©mon.
Swoobat is a blue, bat-like PokÃ©mon. It has fused, pointed ears with striated, lighter colored insides and a pink, heart-shaped snout with a single nostril. 

It evolves from [[Woobat]] with high [i]friendship[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Kororomori[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Woobat]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Drilbur]]

title: woobat
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #527 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a dual type Psychic/Flying PokÃ©mon.
Woobat is a blue, spherical PokÃ©mon, resembling a "Honduran White Bat":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Honduran_white_bat. It is covered in shaggy fur and has a large, piggish nose with a heart-shaped nostril.

It evolves into [[Swoobat]] with high [i]friendship[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Koromori[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Gigalith]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Swoobat]]

title: gigalith
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #526 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Rock type PokÃ©mon.
Gigalith is a blue quadruped PokÃ©mon, with various spiny, crystal-like red features jutting out of its body. Its limbs have gray joints and are topped with red crystalline features, with the two claws on each limb being similar features.

It evolves from [[Boldore]] when traded.
Japanese Name: [b]Gigaiath[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Boldore]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Woobat]]

title: roggenrola
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #524 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Rock type PokÃ©mon.
Roggenrola is a roughly spherical PokÃ©mon discovered a century ago in an earthquake fissure. Its body is blue and covered in large, smooth facets. It has a hexagonal, yellow artifice in the center of its body, leading to a hexagonal opening that functions as an ear. 

It evolves into [[Boldore]].
Japanese Name: [b]Dangoro[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Zebstrika]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Boldore]]

title: zebstrika
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #523 in the National PokÃ©Dex, an Electric type PokÃ©mon.
Zebstrika is a zebra-like PokÃ©mon. Its coat is black with white, jagged stripes all over its body. There is one pointed stripe extending from its nose, two elaborate stripes on its neck and chest, one zigzag stripe each on its jaws, back, and hindquarters, one triangular stripe on each of its thighs, and two stripes banding each of its legs.

It evolves from [[Blitzle]].
Japanese Name: [b]Zebraika[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Blitzle]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Roggenrola]]

title: blitzle
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #522 in the National PokÃ©Dex, an Electric type PokÃ©mon.
Blitzle is a black, zebra-like PokÃ©mon with thick, double-pointed white stripes on its neck, chest, back, and hind legs. It has a rounded muzzle with a large, dark nose and oval, blue eyes with yellow sclera.

It evolves into [[Zebstrika]].
Japanese Name: [b]Shimama[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Unfezant]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Zebstrika]]

title: tranquill
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #520 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a dual type Normal/Flying PokÃ©mon.
Tranquill is an avian PokÃ©mon that is gray with lighter gray and black markings. Its beak and eyes are yellow, and there is dark pink marking above its beak that curves back over the eyes.

It evolves from [[Pidove]] and evolves into [[Unfezant]].
Japanese Name: [b]Hatoboh[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Pidove]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Unfezant]]

title: pidove
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #519 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a dual type Normal/Flying  PokÃ©mon.
Pidove is a mainly gray, pigeon-like PokÃ©mon. It has golden, oval eyes and a tuft of feathers atop its rounded head. It has a short, black beak with a bulbous pink cere, and a black patch on the nape of its neck. 

It evolves into [[Tranquill]].
Japanese Name: [b]Mamepato[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Musharna]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Tranquill]]

title: musharna
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #518 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Psychic type PokÃ©mon.
Musharna is rounded, bipedal PokÃ©mon that has a tapir-like trunk. Its body is light purple, while its head is a pale pink. It has oval, red eyes with three eyelashes and dark pink ovals on its forehead and cheeks. The tips of its four stubby limbs are dark pink. "Dream Mist":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Dream_Mist seeps out of the mark on its forehead.

It evolves from [[Munna]] when exposed to a [i]Moon Stone[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Musharna[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Munna]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Pidove]]

title: panpour
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #515 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Water type PokÃ©mon.
Panpour is a simian, blue-and-cream PokÃ©mon. It has oval eyes that are usually seen closed, large ears with light blue insides, and a tiny, black nose. There is a puffy, wave-like crest on top of its head.

It evolves into [[Simipour]] with a [i]Water Stone[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Hiyappu[/b]

[b]See also:[/b]
[[Pansage]]
[[Pansear]]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Simisear]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Simipour]]

title: simisear
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #514 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Fire type PokÃ©mon.
Simisear is a simian PokÃ©mon that is primarily red. Its ears are broad with orange insides, and it has oval eyes and a small black nose. It has a swirled, flame-like tuft on its head with a smaller tuft on either side of it. 

It evolves from [[Pansear]] with a [i]Fire Stone[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Baokkie[/b]

[b]See also:[/b]
[[Simisage]]
[[Simipour]]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Pansear]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Panpour]]

title: pansear
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #513 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Fire type PokÃ©mon.
Pansear is a simian, red-and-cream PokÃ©mon. Its head is red with a whorled tuft on top. The tuft contains a flame, and can reach temperatures of 600 Â°F (315 Â°C).

It evolves into [[Simisear]] with a [i]Fire Stone[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Baoppu[/b]

[b]See also:[/b]
[[Pansage]]
[[Panpour]]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Simisage]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Simisear]]

title: simisage
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #512 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Grass type PokÃ©mon.
Simisage is a simian PokÃ©mon that is primarily green. It has a pointed, bush-like crest on its head similar to a [[pompadour]]. The leaves of this crest are bitter. Its ears are broad with light green insides, and it has oval eyes and a black nose.

It evolves from [[Pansage]] with a [i]Leaf Stone[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Yanakkie[/b]

[b]See also:[/b]
[[Simisear]]
[[Simipour]]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Pansage]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Pansear]]

title: pansage
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #511 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Grass type PokÃ©mon.
Pansage is a simian, green-and-cream PokÃ©mon. It has oval, black eyes, large ears with light green insides, and a tiny, black nose. There is a broccoli-like sprout atop its head.

It evolves into [[Simisage]] with a [i]Leaf Stone[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Yanappu[/b]

[b]See also[/b]: 
[[Pansear]]
[[Panpour]]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Liepard]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Simisage]]

title: liepard
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #510 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Dark type PokÃ©mon.
Liepard is a slender, purple feline PokÃ©mon speckled with yellow rosettes. Its fur patterning is considered attractive to many Trainers. It has a pink "mask" marking over its eyes, a pink nose, and small yellow markings over its green eyes.

It evolves from [[Purrloin]].
Japanese Name: [b]Lepardas[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Purrloin]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Pansage]]

title: stoutland
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #508 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Normal type PokÃ©mon.
Stoutland is a canine PokÃ©mon with a talent for rescuing people lost at sea or in the mountains. On its face, it has cream-colored fur that forms voluminous, white-tipped plumes and a three-pointed crest.

It evolves from [[Herdier]].
Japanese Name: [b]Mooland[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Herdier]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Purrloin]]

title: herdier
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #507 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Normal type PokÃ©mon.
Herdier is a light brown, canine PokÃ©mon with a short snout. Its face has long, cream fur, which forms a mustache and a three-pointed crest. Its ears are large and perked, and it has a black nose. 

It evolves from [[Lillipup]] and evolves into [[Stoutland]].
Japanese Name: [b]Herderrie[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Lillipup]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Stoutland]]

title: lillipup
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #506 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Normal type PokÃ©mon.
Lillipup is a light brown, canine PokÃ©mon. It has oval, brown eyes, a red nose, and its face covered by an abundance of cream fur. This facial fur can be used for radar, and provides Lillipup with information about its surroundings.

It evolves into [[Herdier]].
Japanese Name: [b]Yorterrie[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Watchog]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Herdier]]

title: watchog
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #505 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Normal type PokÃ©mon.
Watchog is an upright, meerkat-like PokÃ©mon with large cheeks and a single, pointed incisor sticking out of its mouth. It is mainly reddish brown with beige cheeks and neck.

It evolves from [[Patrat]].
Japanese Name: [b]Miruhog[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Patrat]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Lillipup]]

title: patrat
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #504 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Normal type PokÃ©mon.
Patrat is a rodent-like PokÃ©mon that resembles a chipmunk. It is mostly brown with a tan stomach and face. It has a large pointed tooth that sticks out of its mouth. 

It evolves into [[Watchog]].
Japanese Name: [b]Minezumi[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Samurott]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Watchog]]

title: samurott
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #503 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Water type PokÃ©mon.
Samurott is a quadruped, blue, sea lion-like PokÃ©mon. It has two pairs of pointed teeth, one in the upper jaw and one in the lower. 

It evolves from [[Dewott]]
Japanese Name: [b]Daikenki[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Dewott]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Patrat]]

title: dewott
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #502 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Water type PokÃ©mon.
Dewott is a bipedal, otter-like PokÃ©mon that is primarily light blue. It has small black ears, a pointed crest at the back of its head, a red nose, and long white whiskers forming tilted V-shapes.

It evolves from [[Oshawott]] and evolves into [[Samurott]].
Japanese Name: [[Futachimaru]]

[b]See also:[/b]
[[Servine]]
[[Pignite]]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Oshawott]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Samurott]]

title: heatran
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #485 in the National PokÃ©dex, a dual Fire/Steel-type PokÃ©mon.
Heatran is a reddish-brown PokÃ©mon resembling a tortoise and possibly species of insect. It is dotted with orange and gray spots, and it has metal bangles locked on its legs. Its four claws on each of its feet are in a cross formation.
Without the power of the [i]Magma Stone[/i], Heatran would rampage and cause the volcanic crater where it dwells to erupt.
It is the only Legendary PokÃ©mon that can be either male or female.

Japanese Name: [[Heatran]]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Palkia]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Regigigas]]

title: pignite
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #499 in the PokÃ©Dex, a dual type Fire/Fighting PokÃ©mon. Pignite is a bipedal, pig-like PokÃ©mon. Its chubby body is orange with brown bands around its shoulders, sides, belly, hands, and from the back of its head down its snout. Yellow bands encircle its wrists, and swirled yellow designs bulge from its chest.

It evolves from [[Tepig]] and evolves into [[Emboar]].
Japanese Name: [b]Chaoboo[/b]

See also:
[[Servine]]
[[Dewott]]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Tepig]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Emboar]]

title: servine
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #496 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Grass type PokÃ©mon.
Servine is a slim bipedal PokÃ©mon that is primarily green with a cream underside, and narrow red eyes. It has a yellow V-shaped structure that starts at the chest and extends behind the shoulders.

[b]See also[/b]
[[Pignite]]
[[Dewott]]

It evolves from [[Snivy]] and evolves into [[Serperior]].
Japanese Name: [b]Janovy[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Snivy]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Serperior]]

title: darkrai
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #491 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Dark type Mythical PokÃ©mon.
Darkrai is a black, shadow-like PokÃ©mon. It has a small head with a white fog-like ghostly plume billowing from its head covering one of its bright blue eyes, with the portion on its face resembling hair.

It is member of the "Lunar Duo":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Legendary_duo#Lunar_duo alongside [[Cresselia]].
Japanese Name: [b]Darkrai[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Manaphy]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Shaymin]]

title: phione
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #489 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Water type PokÃ©mon.
Phione is a blue PokÃ©mon with a round head and a tiny body. Phione's head is crowned by a flotation sac with a long, ribbon-like antenna. Its mouth is small, and its eyes are large with blue sclera and gray irises.

Although it can be obtained by breeding [[Manaphy]] (or from other Phione with [[Ditto]]) it can't evolve into Manaphy.
It is member of the "Sea Guardians":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Legendary_duo#Sea_guardians with Manaphy. 

Japanese Name: [b]Phione[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Cresselia]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Manaphy]]

title: cresselia
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #488 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Psychic type Legendary PokÃ©mon.
Cresselia has a blue, swan-like body with a yellow underside. It has pink eyes, a dark pink, round tuft on its head, and a pointed, beak-like snout. There are yellow, crescent-shaped ornaments on the sides of its head.
It is always female.

With [[Darkrai]] it is member of the "Lunar Duo":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Legendary_duo#Lunar_duo.

Japanese Name: [b]Crecelia[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Giratina]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Phione]]

title: sally_hartman
body: N5 heavy tank girl in mobile game Panzer Waltz.

title: azelf
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #482 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Psychic type Legendary PokÃ©mon.
Azelf is a small, gray-blue, fairy-like PokÃ©mon. It has two tails that each have a red jewel on them. These are, presumably, two of the jewels which complement the "Red Chain":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Red_Chain. Azelf has a partially cyan face with another red gem encrusted into its forehead. Azelf has a cone-shaped head with elf ear-like protrusions on each side. 

With [[Uxie]] and [[Mesprit]] it is part of the "Lake Guardians":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Lake_guardians in Sinnoh.
It is the bringer of willpower. 

Japanese Name: [b]Agnome[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Mesprit]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Dialga]]

title: uxie
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #480 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Psychic type Legendary PokÃ©mon.
Uxie is a small, gray, fairy-like PokÃ©mon with two gray tails that are each encrusted with a red gem. These are, presumably, two of the jewels which make up the "Red Chain":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Red_Chain. Uxie has a partially yellow face with another red gem encrusted into its forehead.

With [[Mesprit]] and [[Azelf]] it is part of the "Lake Guardians":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Lake_guardians
It is the bringer of knowledge.

Japanese Name: [b]Yuxie[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Rotom]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Mesprit]]

title: dusknoir
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #477 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Ghost type PokÃ©mon.
Dusknoir is a primarily black PokÃ©mon somewhat resembling a cyclops. Its cylindrical head is light gray with a single eye that has a yellow iris and a red pupil. There is a yellow band near the top of its head, and a short, yellow antenna with a disc-shaped tip extends from on top.

It evolves from [[Dusclops]] when traded holding the [i]Reaper Cloths[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Yonoir[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Probopass]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Froslass]]

title: porygon-z
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #474 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Normal type PokÃ©mon.
Although technically a virtual, manmade PokÃ©mon, Porygon-Z does have a physical body. Its head is fuchsia and ovoid in shape with a short, blunt antenna protruding upwards and a blue bill similar to that of a duck. 

It evolves from [[Porygon2]] when traded holding a [i]Dubious Disk[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]PorygonZ[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Mamoswine]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Gallade]]

title: mamoswine
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #473 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a dual type Ice/Ground PokÃ©mon.
Mamoswine resembles a wooly mammoth crossed with a boar. Its brown fur is very thick to endure harsh cold and protect from snow and ice. Its tusks, which are smaller on a female Mamoswine than on a male, are made of pure, solid ice. 

It evolves from [[Piloswine]] when leveled up knowing the move [i]Ancient Power[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Mamoo[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Gliscor]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Porygon-Z]]

title: togekiss
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #468 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a dual type Fairy/Flying PokÃ©mon. Prior to Generation VI, it was a dual type Normal/Flying PokÃ©mon.
Togekiss is a white, avian PokÃ©mon with an ovoid body. While its feet are small and situated closely together, its wings are broad and triangular. Red and blue triangular markings over its underside, and it has a short tail consisting of three feathers.

It evolves from [[Togetic]] when a [i]Shiny stone[/i] is used on it.
Japanese Name: [b]Togekiss[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Magmortar]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Yanmega]]

title: magmortar
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #467 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Fire type PokÃ©mon.
Magmortar is a large, vaguely humanoid, red-and-yellow-striped PokÃ©mon with an egg-shaped body. It has pink lips on its dark face. It has yellow, tubular arms with three small claws on each "hand". 

It evolves from [[Magmar]] when traded holding a [i]Magmarizer[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Booburn[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Electivire]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Togekiss]]

title: electivire
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #466 in the National PokÃ©Dex, an Electric type PokÃ©mon.
Electivire is a humanoid creature covered in yellow fur with black stripes. It appears to lack a neck, and has red eyes, a black spot on its forehead, and a pair of antennae with bulbous tips.

It evolves from [[Electabuzz]] when traded holding an [i]Electirizer[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Elekible[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Tangrowth]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Magmortar]]

title: tangrowth
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #465 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Grass type PokÃ©mon.
Tangrowth is a large PokÃ©mon with a black body wrapped in blue vines. The vines are used to entangle foes and prey.

It evolves from [[Tangela]] when leveled up knowing the move [i]Ancient Power[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Mojumbo[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Rhyperior]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Electivire]]

http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_PokÃ©mon_(441â€“493)#Tangrowth

title: rhyperior
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #464 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a dual type Rock/Ground PokÃ©mon.
Rhyperior is a large, brownish-gray PokÃ©mon with two horns: one on its nose, and another one above it. The upper horn is smaller on a female Rhyperior. It has a club-like tail and its hide is partially covered by orange, rocky plates.

It evolves from [[Rhydon]] when holding a [i]Protector[/i] when it is traded. 
Japanese Name: [b]Dosidon[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Lickilicky]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Tangrowth]]

title: lickilicky
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #463 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Normal type PokÃ©mon.
Lickilicky is a dark pink, rotund PokÃ©mon with a small tail and a long tongue. It has a yellow line pattern on its belly and a white bib-like pattern, making it almost resemble a round baby boy. 

It evolves from [[Lickitung]] when leveled up knowing the move [i]Rollout[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Berobelt[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Magnezone]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Rhyperior]]

title: magneton
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #082 in the National PokÃ©dex, a dual type Electric/Steel PokÃ©mon.
Magneton is the result of three Magnemite being linked together by a strong magnetic force, although a single Magnemite can evolve by itself when no other Magnemite are in the vicinity.

 
It evolves from [[Magnemite]] and evolves into [[Magnezone]] when leveled up in:
Gen IV: "Mt. Coronet":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Mt._Coronet
Gen V:  "Chargestone Cave":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Chargestone_Cave
Gen VI: "Route 13 (Kalos)":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Kalos_Route_13 ([[pokemon_xy|PokÃ©mon XY]]) and "New Mauville":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/New_Mauville ([[pokemon_oras|PokÃ©mon Oras]])
Japanese name: [b]Rarecoil[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Magnemite]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Farfetch'd]]

title: weavile
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #461 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a dual type Ice/Dark PokÃ©mon.
Weavile is a bipedal, weasel-like PokÃ©mon with a pale gray body and several feathery areas. It has a bright red crown and collar made of wide feathers, and a single, thinner feather on each ear. 

It evolves from [[Sneasel]] when leveled up holding a [i]Razor Claw[/i] during the night.
Japanese Name: [b]Manyula[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Abomasnow]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Magnezone]]

title: snover
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #459 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a dual type Grass/Ice PokÃ©mon.
Snover is a creature with a white upper body and brown lower body that resembles a snow-covered tree. It will be two-thirds brown if male and two-thirds white if female.

It evolves into [[Abomasnow]].
Japanese Name: [b]Yukikaburi[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Mantyke]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Abomasnow]]

title: mantyke
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #458 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a dual type Water/Flying PokÃ©mon.
Mantyke resembles a [[manta_ray]]. It has a round body with wide, flat fins. Its back is dark blue, while its underside is light blue. There are two red spots with white outlines and a light blue, curved line on its back.

It evolves into [[Mantine]] when leveled up with a [[Remoraid]] in the party.
Japanese Name: [b]Tamanta[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Lumineon]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Snover]]

title: lumineon
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #457 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Water type PokÃ©mon.
Lumineon is a fish-like PokÃ©mon with dark blue scales. Its eyes are deep pink, and its face and eyelids are light blue. It has two pairs of large pectoral fins that resemble butterfly wings. 

It evolves from [[Finneon]].
Japanese Name: [b]Neolant[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Finneon]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Mantyke]]

title: finneon
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #456 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Water type PokÃ©mon.
Finneon is a small fish PokÃ©mon with an ellipsoid body. The bottom half of its body is light-blue while the top half is black. A purple stripe runs across Finneon's horizontal length. 

It evolves into [[Lumineon]].
Japanese Name: [b]Keikouo[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Carnivine]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Lumineon]]

title: toxicroak
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #454 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a dual type Fighting/Poison PokÃ©mon.
Toxicroak is a dark blue and teal, bipedal PokÃ©mon resembling a poison dart frog. Its head bears a gently-upward curling spike which seems to be a part of the skull. Its eyes are bright yellow, sinister and intimidating, with a small snake-like pupil.

It evolves from [[Croagunk]].
Japanese Name: [b]Dokurog[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Croagunk]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Carnivine]]

title: croagunk
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #453 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a dual type Fighting/Poison PokÃ©mon.
Croagunk is a dark blue, bipedal PokÃ©mon that resembles a poison dart frog. It has yellow eyes, which are surrounded by black markings. There are orange, expandable pouches on its cheeks, and its teeth are wide and flat.

It evolves into [[Toxicroak]].
Japanese Name: [b]Gureggru[/b]

title: sekihan_(tradition)
body:
èµ¤é£¯ ([i]sekihan[/i], literally, red rice) is a mixture of glutinous [[rice]] and azuki beans that is steamed and eaten seasoned with sesame and salt. 
In Japan, it is customary to eat sekihan at any celebration. It is also widely canned as emergency rations due to its high nutritional value. 
Recipes and customs vary from region to region, with some regions having a tradition of eating sekihan after a misfortune, for example. 

At one time in Japan, a girl's first menstruation was celebrated by the entire family eating sekihan, often to the confusion of her younger siblings. 
Even now, after this custom has been abandoned, insinuation of a connection between the start of menstruation and sekihan sometimes appears manga as a running gag. In some cases â€the first menstruationâ€ is replaced by â€the lost of virginityâ€ to make things more funny.

title: relife
body:
ReLIFE

A very popular ongoing webcomic series by [[Yayoi Sou]] that serialized in Comico. It is the first series ever from Comico that was published as a tankoubon volume with the first volume published by Earth Star Comics on 12 August 2014. An anime adaption by TMS Entertainment has been announced for the Summer 2016 season.
 
The story follows [[Kaizaki Arata]], a 27 year old jobless man who fails at every job interviews he had after quitting his last company which he only last 3 months. His life changes after he met [[Yoake Ryou]] of the ReLife Research Institute, who offer him a drug that can change his appearance to 17 years old again and to became a subject in a 1-year experiment in which he begin his life as a high school student again.

title: provisional_plate
body: A type of vehicle plate, similar in appearance to an L-plate. Much like the [[shoshinsha mark]] in Japan, it's designed to show that the driver has completed their learner's qualifications, but they're still new to driving. In some countries such as [[Australia]], [[Malaysia]] and [[Hong Kong]], new drivers are legally required for a certain amount of time to display these plates on any vehicles they drive, while other countries such as the [[United Kingdom]] tend to recommend the use of these plates without actually making it mandatory.

title: chibita
body:
Character from [i][[Osomatsu-kun]][/i] and its spinoffs.

A short boy with [[bald|no hair]]. Often the Matsunos' rival, he schemes against them and creates plans to get at their throats. He is sometimes portrayed as the target for the sextuplets' bullying. His favorite food is [[oden]].

Along with [[Iyami]], he became the main focus of the 1980's anime and later chapters of the original manga. By [i][[Osomatsu-san]][/i], he has been reduced to side character status, but now owns an oden stall.

body:
Character from [i][[Osomatsu-kun]][/i] and its spinoffs.

A scheming man with abnormally large [[buck teeth]]. He is obsessed with France, and despite never having been there, pretends to be knowledgeable on it.

He is most known for his "[[sheeeh!]]" pose and catchphrase, often used as an indication of surprise. Both he and [[Chibita]] were the main focus of the 1980's adaptation and later chapters of the original manga.
